{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SJ3Eb7WNmRTFD5C4heGtA4","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive summary document for the user.\n\n## Integration Pattern Exploration Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the anchor-client package and program ID integration pattern. Here's what you need to know to replicate the pattern for closecall:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Anchor-Client Package Structure**\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/`\n\n**Current Files**:\n- `index.ts` — barrel export (544 bytes)\n- `coinflip.json` — IDL (812 lines)\n- `coinflip.ts` — type definitions (17,745 bytes)\n- `lordofrngs.json` — IDL (1,320 lines)\n- `lordofrngs.ts` — type definitions (28,610 bytes)\n- `platform.json` — IDL (2,780 bytes)\n- `platform.ts` — type definitions (3,009 bytes)\n- `fairness_test.json` / `fairness_test.ts` — (9,401 / 9,624 bytes)\n\n**Missing**: closecall.json and closecall.ts\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Index.ts Barrel Export Pattern**\n\n```typescript\n// IDL JSON (runtime values) — committed copies, not build artifacts\nimport CoinflipIDL from \"./coinflip.json\" with { type: \"json\" };\nimport LordofrngsIDL from \"./lordofrngs.json\" with { type: \"json\" };\nimport PlatformIDL from \"./platform.json\" with { type: \"json\" };\n\n// Type-safe IDL types (compile-time)\nexport type { Coinflip } from \"./coinflip.js\";\nexport type { Lordofrngs } from \"./lordofrngs.js\";\nexport type { Platform } from \"./platform.js\";\n\n// Re-export IDLs as typed constants\nexport { CoinflipIDL, LordofrngsIDL, PlatformIDL };\n```\n\n**Pattern to replicate for Closecall**:\n- Add `import ClosecallIDL from \"./closecall.json\" with { type: \"json\" };`\n- Add `export type { Closecall } from \"./closecall.js\";`\n- Add `export { ClosecallIDL };` to the re-export\n\n---\n\n### 3. **IDL JSON Files**\n\nAll IDL JSON files follow the standard Anchor IDL format:\n- **address**: Program deployment address\n- **metadata**: name, version, spec\n- **instructions**: All on-chain instructions with discriminators, accounts, args\n- **accounts**: Account types with discriminators\n- **events**: Event definitions\n- **errors**: Error codes and messages (offset by 6100 base)\n- **types**: Struct/enum definitions\n\n**For Closecall**:\n- **Address**: `8TXq2XyHsk5AAMkoyk5QtG25xyyY7rTMHXrJRHRwjUpA`\n- **File size**: 1,041 lines\n- **Instructions**: `create_round`, `force_close`, `join_round`, `resolve`\n- **Accounts**: `closeCallConfig`, `closeCallRound`\n- **Types**: `roundPhase`, `outcome`, `roundSettled` (event), etc.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Type Definition Files (*.ts)**\n\nEach `.ts` file is **auto-generated** by Anchor's IDL extraction. The structure is:\n- Comment header explaining it's a type helper, not the actual IDL\n- `export type ProgramName = { ... }` with full camelCase IDL structure\n- Hard-coded program address at the top (e.g., `\"address\": \"BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx\"`)\n\n**For Closecall**:\n- Already generated at: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/target/types/closecall.ts` (1,048 lines)\n- Exports `export type Closecall = { ... }`\n- Address: `8TXq2XyHsk5AAMkoyk5QtG25xyyY7rTMHXrJRHRwjUpA`\n\n---\n\n### 5. **How Program IDs are Defined in Game-Engine**\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/`\n\n**Pattern for Coinflip** (`coinflip.ts`):\n```typescript\nimport { PublicKey } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\nimport { CoinflipIDL } from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\n\nexport const COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n  CoinflipIDL.address\n);\n```\n\n**Pattern for Lord of the RNGs** (`lordofrngs.ts`):\n```typescript\nimport { PublicKey } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\nimport { LordofrngsIDL } from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\n\nexport const LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n  LordofrngsIDL.address\n);\n```\n\n**Key insight**: Program IDs are extracted at runtime from the IDL's hardcoded address field, not hardcoded in game-engine.\n\n**For Closecall**: You would follow the same pattern:\n```typescript\nimport { PublicKey } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\nimport { ClosecallIDL } from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\n\nexport const CLOSECALL_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n  ClosecallIDL.address\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Index.ts in Game-Engine**\n\nThe main export file (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/index.ts`) exports:\n- `COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID`\n- `LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID`\n- PDA derivation functions for each game (e.g., `getMatchPda`, `getRoundPda`, `getConfigPda`)\n- Type definitions and helper functions\n\n**Pattern**: Each game has its own module file exporting its program ID and PDA helpers.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Existing Build Artifacts**\n\n**Closecall IDL and Types are READY**:\n- ✅ `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/target/idl/closecall.json` (1,041 lines)\n- ✅ `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/target/types/closecall.ts` (1,048 lines)\n\nThese were generated by the Anchor build and are ready to be copied into anchor-client/src.\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Summary of Files to Create/Modify**\n\nTo integrate Closecall fully, you need:\n\n1. **Copy to anchor-client/src/**:\n   - `closecall.json` (from `solana/target/idl/closecall.json`)\n   - `closecall.ts` (from `solana/target/types/closecall.ts`)\n\n2. **Update** `packages/anchor-client/src/index.ts`:\n   - Add import for ClosecallIDL\n   - Add export type for Closecall\n   - Add ClosecallIDL to re-exports\n\n3. **Create** `packages/game-engine/src/closecall.ts`:\n   - Export `CLOSECALL_PROGRAM_ID` derived from ClosecallIDL.address\n   - Export PDA derivation functions (e.g., `getRoundPda`, `getConfigPda`)\n   - Export any game-specific helper functions\n\n4. **Update** `packages/game-engine/src/index.ts`:\n   - Export `CLOSECALL_PROGRAM_ID`\n   - Export closecall PDA helpers\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Key Details from Closecall IDL**\n\n- **Program Address**: `8TXq2XyHsk5AAMkoyk5QtG25xyyY7rTMHXrJRHRwjUpA`\n- **PDA Seeds**:\n  - Config: `[\"closecall_config\"]`\n  - Round: `[\"cc_round\", roundId]` (8-byte round ID)\n- **Instructions**: createRound, forceClose, joinRound, resolve\n- **Types**: outcome enum (pending, green, red, refund), roundSettled event\n- **Program features**: Pyth oracle integration for BTC price oracle\n\n---\n\n### File Paths Summary\n\n- **Anchor-client barrel export**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/index.ts`\n- **IDL storage (JSON)**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/*.json`\n- **Type files (TS)**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/*.ts`\n- **Game-engine program IDs**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/coinflip.ts` and `lordofrngs.ts`\n- **Game-engine index**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/game-engine/src/index.ts`\n- **Build artifacts (ready to copy)**:\n  - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/target/idl/closecall.json`\n  - `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/target/types/closecall.ts`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a44c621c39748e482 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 68771\ntool_uses: 28\nduration_ms: 69118</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ca44bf8e-b3d0-49be-94bb-b1cdc247762d","uuid":"ddca7e33-5141-4a09-8722-30263e12f3d3","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the anchor-client package to understand how coinflip and lordofrngs IDL/types are integrated. I need to see:\n\n1. `sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/index.ts` — the barrel export\n2. How `coinflip.json` and `lordofrngs.json` IDLs are stored in `packages/anchor-client/src/`\n3. How the types files (`coinflip.ts`, `lordofrngs.ts`) are structured\n4. `packages/